          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to extend measurements of the",
                "relative cross sections to energies other than",
                "thermal it is necessary to use more massive foils of",
                "239Pu which are not necessarily thin for the emission",
                "of fission fragments. The effective mass of the 239Pu",
                "sample used in these experiments was found to be 17.2",
                "micrograms by measuring the relative fission rates of",
                "this sample and a 17.9 microgram thin foil of 235U",
                "simultaneously irradiated by slow neutrons. These",
                "foils were mounted back to back on opposite sides of",
                "the high voltage electrode of an ionization",
                "comparison chamber containing air at atmospheric",
                "pressure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors shown in the",
                "239Pu(n,f)/235U(n,f) figure are calculated from the",
                "statistics of the new under of fission fragments",
                "counted in each case except for the highest-energy",
                "point. In this case some of the error arises from",
                "uncertainty of the amount of 238U present in the 235U",
                "sample since at this neutron energy approximately 1/3",
                "of the fissions were of the 238U in the sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
